  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Static pedobarography is routinely used for pre- and postoperative questions regarding
      plantar foot pressure. This Investigation does insufficiently detect dynamic Forces. Hence,
      dynamic pedobarography might give some important insights in detecting plantar foot pressure
      after forefoot reconstruction.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
